Basic
In js for printing the output use console.log.
example: console.log("Hello World")

use keyword let for giving variables
ex:let num=0;
And use const keyword for constant variables.It will not change the value afetr we assign it.
ex:const pi=3.14

we use "typeof" in console.log for know about it is string or number.
ex:let num=1234556;
let name="Arun";
console.log(typeof name)
output---->string


number+string=string
number-string=number

In javascript the boolean function is make true or false
false-->0,"",undefined value,null.

In variables number and string are combine we want only output number and use "parseInt"
ex:parseInt(123 Arun)

== -->It takes only data
===  --->It takes both data and types


For using if else statement, there  is a keyword ?:
   //let arr=8;
     let res;

     res=arr%2==0?"even":"odd"
     console.log(res)

//switch statement

let day="sat";

switch(day){
    case'monday':
    console.log("7am")
    break;
    case'tuesday':
    console.log("8am")
    break;
    case'wed':
    console.log("8am")
    break;
    console.log("9am")
    break;
    case'fri':
    console.log("9am")
    break;
    case'sat':
    console.log("4am")
    break;
}

